{"word":"ἄντομαι","slug":"ἄντομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄντομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀντί'><el>ἀντί</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>impf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>=<a href='S:ἀντάω'><el>ἀντάω</el></a> <i>to meet</i>, in battle, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>διπλόος ἤντετο θώρηξ</el> the breastplate doubled (by the belt) <i>met</i> or <i>stopped</i> (the dart), <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <el>ἀντιάζω 1. 2</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to approach with prayers, entreat</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}